<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
      Beaver is a developer tool — it intentionally runs OUTSIDE the
      App Sandbox so it can:

      * Bind a TCP socket on port 9080 for incoming SDK connections
        (the sandbox network.server entitlement works, but combined
        with Sparkle's installer XPC the sandbox needs additional
        mach-lookup exceptions that aren't worth the complexity)
      * Let Sparkle launch its installer subprocess to apply updates
        — Sparkle 2's XPC services can't bring themselves up under
        a sandboxed parent without exception entitlements
      * Read/write the user-selected files from Import / Export
        without going through the security-scoped resource dance

      Hardened runtime is still ON (set via ENABLE_HARDENED_RUNTIME
      in the pbxproj), which is what notarization actually requires.
      Sandbox is orthogonal to notarization.
    -->
</dict>
</plist>
